body: @ianlancetaylor On a fresh CentOS container, the difference between the version of `go vet` that shipped with `go1.4.2` and the current version from `go get` is that the new version does not pick up on some `-composites`. Running both with `-v` doesn't show me any import errors for those packages or files. I think there may be an issue with `godeps` but I'd expect `go vet` to complain about that with `-v` set? I'll ask `godeps` authors if they know.
